title: Daniel Harwi Memorial 27th Annual Lower Providence
description: Daniel Harwi Memorial 27th Annual Lower Providence Spring Classic Criterium
course: Criterium event in Lower Providence Township
notes:
PARKING UPDATE - ALL RACE Parking is in the same new location as last year on the outside of the course this year. No parking in the lots you may have grown accustomed to as we've worked with the township to make this race safer and an institution for Lower Providence as they've given us a permanent parking opportunity. Let's not make the businesses in this part resent us by parking in their lots.

Race parking is in a parking lot on the corner of Van Buren Ave and Adams Ave (aka turn #4). There are two lots to choose from. The best way is to turn from Audubon Road onto Adams Ave. This will bring into the office park. Proceed to what is turn #4 of the race course. On your left is race parking. 

Also if you are coming in off of Rittenhouse Road, you could turn onto Van Buren Ave and parking will be on your left at the second driveway. Registration will be near start finish and in this lot to keep things compact/easy.  As well, registration will be in this lot to keep things compact/easy.

Please listen to the marshalls when they direct you to the parking location.

As always, this is a PCA / BAR race (www.pacycling.org)

Many thanks to our four sponsors of the event:

1.) The Performance Lab powered by the Rothman Institute (www.theperformancelabnj.com)
2.) Caffeinated Cyclist (www.tccyclist.com)
3.) Pennsylvania's Women's Racing Series (www.pawomensracing.blogspot.com)
4.) Lower Providence Township (www.lowerprovidence.org)


Without supporters of this support we'd not have great events to gather and compete at. Please make your support of these sponsors known by going to their websites or storefronts and letting them know you recognize them as a stand-up company who supports what you like to do.  That in itself will provide them with the ROI to continuing to help support cycling events in the Mid-Atlantic.

Couple things to note:

1) This is one of the top three highest attended criteriums in Pennsylvania - (last year had 400+ racers!!!).
2) This is the longest running criterium in the state.
3) All races are designed to be USCF upgrade worthy (As all races SHOULD be)!

Women's events - PA Women's Series: a season-long points competition open to all women racers of all ages.  Racers do not have to live in PA to participate in the Series.   The Women's PA BAR series is open to PA resident riders only.  For more information, go to pawomensracing.blogspot.com.     

 The older Junior categories are Junior Pro Cycling Tour qualifiers. Go to http://www.procyclingtour.com/philadelphia.junior.cfm for more specifics on these national junior series.
 
Fine Print/Details: 

    $5 Late Fee in effect as of 4/12 11:45PM EST (register by Fri night. we don't want your extra $5, but we do want to know how the registration is going to play out. Quoting Jerry Maquire, "Help ME, Help You."
    Payout is 1/2 amount listed if <25 racers in event (exceptions-women, juniors).
    Race is run rain or shine.
    Promoter reserves the right to shorten, combine or alter events as needed due to weather, timing and other uncontrollable circumstances (crash delays, injuries, needs of Police, EMTs, Acts of God).
    Course: 1 Mile, Clockwise, Mostly Flat, 4-corner crit with Free Laps/wheel pit. 
    Registration opens at 7:15 am.
    No aero bars.  Approved helmets must be worn..
    All USCF rules apply. 
    Entry fee includes insurance surcharge of $2 for USCF & $5 for Citizens. 
    Promoter reserves the right to combine or cancel races if less than 12 racers register for an event.
    Masters races for Cats 1-4 only.
directions: Directions:  Go to www.mapquest.com and type in directions from your location to the corner of Van Buren Ave & Adams Ave., Norristown, PA 19403

title: Mon-Tour
description:
The Mon-Tour Road Races have been in existance for 7 years.  Created by local cycling enthusiasts and clubs as the best route to include every hill in the county and give yourself a real challenge of climbing.

The full course description, maps, and complete information is listed on the website at the following link: http://www.rivertownscyclingclassic.com/montour.php
course:
The entire course is beautiful rural Pennsylvania roads. Most are in good condition, but some vary from year to year.  Be prepared for anything, but at the minimum: some gravel sections (but not a lot).  Lots of hills and rolling farm land.  Only a few intersection crossings that necessitate slower speed crossings.

See a good map here:
http://www.mapmyrun.com/us/danville-pa/mon-tour-route-94568277
registration:
Organizers have decided on three category options:
Cat 1. 2 & 3 at the 82 mile distance.
Cat 3 & 4 at the 48 mile distance
Masters 45+ at the 82 mile distance.

All registration tasks, questions, comments and other business will take place at the Expo location in the Headquarters tent.  This is located at the Iron Town Corporate Park in Danville, PA on the corner of Railroad Street and Market Street.

You can register for these races here:
https://www.bikereg.com/mon-tour-sanctioned
notes:
This is our 7th running of the 82 mile race.  It has always been a citizens race in the past.  Organizers are trying the santioning categories this year, to gauge demand.  If we have a good turn-out, more categories will be added next year.

This race is part of a weekend long celebration of cycling.  There is an expo, vendors, and multiple racing opportunities over the entire weekend - all incorporated with a Fall Arts festival in Danville.  We hope you will make this first weekend in September one of your "must do" events each season.
directions:
The Address is Railroad Street and Market Street in Danville, PA.  The expo/registration tent is located in that location and should be the first stop for all racers. It's a short drive down Route 54 from Interstate 80.

Get full directions using this link: http://rivertownscyclingclassic.com/directions.php

title: Nittany Track (Collegiate, High School and OPEN racing)
West Chester Cross Classic
course: Classic cyclocross course with two sets of barriers and variable terrain mostly grass, with some pavement. The 2.2 mile closed course is great for spectators. Course will be flowing and challenging, making use of natural run-ups, off cambers sections, and lots of cornering. Course is designed by angry Bob Reuther, local cross legend and long time advocate of local cycling.
registration:
Pre-registration will be open on bikereg.com until October 17, 2013 11:00PM.
         There is a $10 late fee for day-of registration.
         Day of Registration and sign-in will be open at 8AM and will close 30 min prior to each race.
         A USAC license is required to participate in this race, day-of and annual licenses will be available for purchase at registration.
         Additional races - only $10!
         Registration price includes $3 USAC insurance fee.
notes:
Amenities:
         Registration will be at tent or inside Rustin High School if weather unfavorable
         First 250 riders to register will receive a gift bag with a Specialized water bottle & nutrition samples.
         There will be indoor permanent bathroom facilities with showers.
         Bike wash will be available.
         We will also have a concession stand set up.  Bring some cash for some goodies and help out a good cause. 
     Alcohol is NOT PERMITTED on School property. Violators will be asked to leave immediately, forfeiting any race fees.  Please be responsible and discard of waste / recycle.

Call-up Protocol: 
         Call-ups will only be awarded by promoter discretion. We will try to utilize 2014 series standings or 2012 final standings.
         Staging will begin 10 minutes prior to each race

 Lapped Riders:
Lapped riders will finish on the same lap as the leaders. Riders in danger of being lapped must yield to oncoming racers and are not to interfere with their progress or trail behind them.

 Technical Pit:
A double sided pit will be marked and available approximately halfway through the course. If riders enter the pit, they must make some sort of exchange or mechanical adjustment.

Results:
Results will be posted at the registration area. Results will be made final 15 minutes after being posted. Podium, awards, and photos will occur roughly a half hour after each race.

Note:
         The course will be open for inspection and warm-up at approximately 8:00am.
         Every racer must have an approved helmet.
         Mountain bikes will be allowed WITHOUT bar ends.
         No aero bars. 
         Check out our Website for updates and photos!

Disclaimer:
The Promoter reserves the right to combine categories, change times, etc.
directions:
Address:  Bayard Rustin High School
1100 Shiloh Road
West Chester, PA 19382

description: One day cyclocross racing in Pottstown, Pennsylvania, hosted by the Sly Fox brewery.

registration: Registration is via BikeReg.com - day off registration will be available subject to space still being open.
directions: Please follow normal directions to the Sly Fox Tasting Room, 331 Circle of Progress Dr, Pottstown, PA 19464 and follow signs to the race parking.
